      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Key Features -->
  <div class="box mb-6">
    <h2 class="title is-3 mb-4">Key Features & Highlights</h2>
    
    <div class="columns is-multiline">
      <div class="column is-half">
        <div class="notification is-dark">
          <h4 class="title is-6 has-text-ruby">Human-in-the-Loop Workflow</h4>
          <p>
            Candidates are automatically detected and prepared, but PR creation requires explicit human approval.
            This ensures oversight while automating tedious research and validation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="column is-half">
        <div class="notification is-dark">
          <h4 class="title is-6 has-text-ruby">Fail-Closed Safety Model</h4>
          <p>
            When parsing, version resolution, or validation encounters ambiguity, the system blocks the candidate
            instead of guessing. Errors are logged to <code>SystemEvent</code> for investigation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="column is-half">
        <div class="notification is-dark">
          <h4 class="title is-6 has-text-ruby">Multi-Source Vulnerability Data</h4>
          <p>
            Ingests from GHSA, OSV, and ruby-lang RSS feeds. Cross-references advisories with official announcements
            for comprehensive coverage and validation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="column is-half">
        <div class="notification is-dark">
          <h4 class="title is-6 has-text-ruby">Rate Limiting & Cooldowns</h4>
          <p>
            Multiple caps (per-gem, per-branch, global hourly/daily) prevent accidental spam to ruby/ruby.
            Rejection cooldown periods enforce waiting time after maintainer feedback.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="column is-half">
        <div class="notification is-dark">
          <h4 class="title is-6 has-text-ruby">Real-Time PR Synchronization</h4>
          <p>
            Continuously syncs PR status, comments, and reviews from GitHub (every 5 minutes for open PRs).
            Detects maintainer feedback and updates local records automatically.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="column is-half">
        <div class="notification is-dark">
          <h4 class="title is-6 has-text-ruby">Comprehensive Audit Trail</h4>
          <p>
            Every operation, error, and noteworthy event is logged to <code>SystemEvent</code>.
            Admin dashboard provides full visibility into system behavior and decision-making.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="column is-half">
        <div class="notification is-dark">
          <h4 class="title is-6 has-text-ruby">LLM-Assisted Decision Making</h4>
          <p>
            Uses DeepSeek for complex scenarios (conflicting versions, risk prioritization) but validates all outputs.
            Tracks resolution source (auto/llm/manual) for transparency.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="column is-half">
        <div class="notification is-dark">
          <h4 class="title is-6 has-text-ruby">Single-Line Diff Validation</h4>
          <p>
            All PRs are validated to change exactly one line in <code>gems/bundled_gems</code>.
            <code>DiffValidator</code> ensures no unexpected changes slip through.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Why This Project -->
  <div class="box mb-6">
    <h2 class="title is-3 mb-4">Why This Project</h2>
    
    <div class="columns">
      <div class="column">
        <h3 class="title is-5 has-text-ruby mb-3">Motivation</h3>
        <p class="mb-3">
          I wanted to tackle a real problem in the Ruby ecosystem: keeping bundled gems secure requires constant vigilance
          across multiple vulnerability sources, Ruby maintenance branches, and rapid response when advisories are published.
        </p>
        <p>
          This project demonstrates how automation can augment human decision-making without replacing it—especially
          in security-critical domains where mistakes have consequences.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="column">
        <h3 class="title is-5 has-text-ruby mb-3">Learning Goals</h3>
        <div class="content">
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Rails 8 & Modern Patterns:</strong> Solid Queue, multi-DB setup, Hotwire/Turbo</li>
            <li><strong>LLM Integration:</strong> Practical AI usage with validation and fail-safe design</li>
            <li><strong>GitHub Automation:</strong> Complex workflows with gh CLI, SSH, and API integration</li>
            <li><strong>DevOps:</strong> Kamal deployment, Docker, multi-environment configuration</li>
            <li><strong>Service Architecture:</strong> Clean boundaries, testable services, observable systems</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-5">
      <h3 class="title is-5 has-text-ruby mb-3">Technical Challenges Solved</h3>
      <div class="columns is-multiline">
        <div class="column is-half">
          <div class="box is-compact">
            <h4 class="title is-6">Version Resolution Conflicts</h4>
            <p class="is-size-7">
              When multiple advisories suggest different fix versions, used LLM to analyze CVE details and recommend
              the minimum version that fixes all issues, with confidence scoring.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="column is-half">
          <div class="box is-compact">
            <h4 class="title is-6">Multi-Source Data Reconciliation</h4>
            <p class="is-size-7">
              GHSA and OSV use different formats and identifiers. Built a normalization layer that deduplicates and
              cross-references with ruby-lang announcements.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="column is-half">
          <div class="box is-compact">
            <h4 class="title is-6">Resumable Background Jobs</h4>
            <p class="is-size-7">
              Designed jobs to be idempotent and resumable. Evaluation can fail mid-way and resume from where it left off
              without duplicating work or corrupting state.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="column is-half">
          <div class="box is-compact">
            <h4 class="title is-6">SSH Key Management in Containers</h4>
            <p class="is-size-7">
              PRs push to fork via SSH. Implemented secure key mounting and host key acceptance with proper
              <code>GIT_SSH_COMMAND</code> configuration in Docker.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

